The paper focuses on physical human-robot interaction and the use of affective communication to enhance trust and counteract operational error. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) categories. Additionally, the use of a humanoid robot assistant and the exploration of human-like characteristics suggest that the paper may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. Finally, the study involves an omelet-making task, which could be considered a form of task planning or scheduling, suggesting that the paper may also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SD) category.
